      {
        "id": 277545,
        "name": "",
        "username": "desert_nip",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/ccd318/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-10-19T19:44:51.277Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Yes, I agree that “unsend” would not be a good choice of words, since the message has, in fact, been sent already and “unsending” it is not an option.</p>\n<p>However, I agree that deleting a message for yourself should maybe not disable the option to delete for everyone. However, I’m not sure if the message ID (which is needed for deleting for everyone) is still saved after deleting it for yourself.</p>\n<p>To reduce the chances of choosing the wrong option, I would suggest simply changing the order to the one android has, which is:</p>\n<p>“delete for me”</p>\n<p>“cancel”</p>\n<p>“delete for everyone”</p>",
